# PART 3: Cross-System (Together) — Inspection & Plan

## Current Integration

```
WhatsApp Bot (Python/FastAPI)
    ↓ POST /api/chatbot/intake (with cv file + candidate data)
Recruitment System Backend (Node.js/Express)
    ↓ Creates/updates candidate + application records
PostgreSQL Database
    ↓ Serves data to
React Frontend
```

## Findings

### ✅ What's Working Well
- **Sync mechanism**: [recruitment_sync.py](file:///d:/Dewan%20Project/Chatbot/whatsapp-recruitment-bot/app/services/recruitment_sync.py) → [chatbot-intake.js](file:///d:/Dewan%20Project/recruitment-system/backend/src/routes/chatbot-intake.js) with API key auth
- **Payload structure**: Phone, name, email, language, source, experience, job, country, CV data
- **Retry logic**: Failed syncs saved with `pending_retry` status, retried on startup
- **Duplicate detection**: Phone-based lookup before insert (update if exists)

### ⚠️ Issues Found

#### 1. CV File Transfer
- The sync sends CV as base64 in JSON body — large CVs may hit request size limits
- **Fix**: Verify max request body size in Express config; consider multipart upload for large files

#### 2. Mismatch Data Flow
- Chatbot calculates [mismatches](file:///d:/Dewan%20Project/Chatbot/whatsapp-recruitment-bot/app/chatbot.py#970-1006) in [_calculate_mismatches()](file:///d:/Dewan%20Project/Chatbot/whatsapp-recruitment-bot/app/chatbot.py#970-1006) and includes in sync payload
- Backend saves to `metadata.mismatches` in candidates table
- Frontend [JobCandidates](file:///d:/Dewan%20Project/recruitment-system/frontend/src/pages/JobCandidates.jsx#49-329) reads metadata — need to verify this data flow works end-to-end
- **Fix**: Trace and verify the complete mismatch data flow

#### 3. Job Cache Synchronization
- Chatbot bootstraps job cache from `/api/chatbot/jobs` on startup
- If new jobs are added to the recruitment system, chatbot needs to refresh cache
- **Fix**: Verify periodic cache refresh exists (see `refresh_job_cache` in [knowledge.py](file:///d:/Dewan%20Project/Chatbot/whatsapp-recruitment-bot/app/knowledge.py))

